4. Why Humans Use Stories for This

Stories solve three coordination problems:

Compression

Complex plans fit into a simple arc.

Memory

People remember characters better than spreadsheets.

Alignment

Multiple people can move toward the same goal without full communication.

That’s why companies, religions, movements, and brands all run on narrative.

